class Solution {
    static int countNodes(int i) {
        int result = (int)Math.pow(2, i-1);
        return result;
    }
}

EXPLAINATION:
💡 Key Concept:
In a binary tree, each node can have at most 2 children.
The maximum number of nodes at level i (where levels start from 1) is given by:

Max nodes at level 
𝑖
=
2
𝑖
−
1
Max nodes at level i=2 
i−1
 
🔢 Examples:
Level (i)	Max Nodes (2^(i-1))
1	1
2	2
3	4
4	8
5	16
6	32

